      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HAYDEN'S MILK (8) used the rails draw to advantage to get home last time at Angle Park over 342m (19.76), scoring by half a length. Can continue winning ways. UP HILL SHILOH (1) rocketed out of the boxes with a strong early sectional but gathered in and finished in the minors when second (23.01) at this track over 400m. Expected to be in this for a long way. VICTA KERLE (2) last appeared when too good (22.99) over 395m at Murray Bridge on January 11. Resumes after finishing fifth (22.99) at Murray Bridge over 395m six months ago. Solid record here winning two races. Meets a moderate line up and should run well. OUR LAURA ROSE (4) was unplaced here last start but gets her chance to atone.",
